Description: The  newly discovered double QSO HE 0047−1756 displays several properties that make it a showpiece gravitationally lensed object rather than a binary QSO: The identical (within ±30 km s−1) redshifts of the two quasar images; the similar emission line proﬁles; the detection of a galaxy located between the two QSO components; and the tentative discovery of a partial Einstein ring.
Name: HE0047-1756
